  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "397cb9cd",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 0
   },
   "source": [
    ".. index:: Methods; Stabilized Discontinuous Galerkin\n",
    "\n",
    "The dune-fem-dg module can either used stabilizer DG methods to solve\n",
    "this type of problem or higher order FV methods based on linear\n",
    "reconstruction. The following function uses a finite-volume space when\n",
    "order=0 and a dg space with orthonormal polynomials otherwise.\n",
    "Note that when a limiter is then used in the scheme, the finite-volume\n",
    "scheme will use linear reconstruction:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "fe84c852",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.801373Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.801115Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.804455Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.803610Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def getSpace( gv, order ):\n",
    "    return finiteVolume( gridView, dimRange=4 ) if order==0 else\\\n",
    "           dgonb( gridView, dimRange=4, order=order )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f061fe9e",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 0
   },
   "source": [
    "Basic model for hyperbolic conservation law"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "70122b3c",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.806023Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.805865Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.811176Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.810495Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class Model:\n",
    "    gamma = 1.4\n",
    "    # helper function\n",
    "    def toPrim(U):\n",
    "        v = as_vector( [U[i]/U[0] for i in range(1,3)] )\n",
    "        kin = dot(v,v) * U[0] / 2\n",
    "        pressure = (Model.gamma-1)*(U[3]-kin)\n",
    "        return U[0], v, pressure\n",
    "\n",
    "    # interface methods for model\n",
    "    @classmethod\n",
    "    def F_c(cls,t,x,U):\n",
    "        rho, v, p = Model.toPrim(U)\n",
    "        return as_matrix( [\n",
    "                  [rho*v[0], rho*v[1]],\n",
    "                  [rho*v[0]*v[0] + p, rho*v[0]*v[1]],\n",
    "                  [rho*v[0]*v[1], rho*v[1]*v[1] + p],\n",
    "                  [(U[3]+p)*v[0], (U[3]+p)*v[1]] ] )\n",
    "\n",
    "    # simple 'outflow' boundary conditions on all boundaries\n",
    "    boundary = {range(1,5): BndValue(lambda t,x,U: U)}\n",
    "\n",
    "    # interface method needed for LLF and time step control\n",
    "    @classmethod\n",
    "    def maxWaveSpeed(cls,t,x,U,n):\n",
    "        rho, v, p = Model.toPrim(U)\n",
    "        return abs(dot(v,n)) + sqrt(Model.gamma*p/rho)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "90550366",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 0
   },
   "source": [
    ".. index:: Methods; Limiter\n",
    "\n",
    "Add methods for limiting"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "298581c0",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.812939Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.812765Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.817173Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.816292Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def velocity(cls,t,x,U):\n",
    "    _, v ,_ = Model.toPrim(U)\n",
    "    return v\n",
    "def physical(cls,t,x,U):\n",
    "    rho, _, p = Model.toPrim(U)\n",
    "    return conditional( rho>1e-8, conditional( p>1e-8 , 1, 0 ), 0 )\n",
    "def jump(cls,t,x,U,V):\n",
    "    _,_, pL = Model.toPrim(U)\n",
    "    _,_, pR = Model.toPrim(V)\n",
    "    return (pL - pR)/(0.5*(pL + pR))\n",
    "Model.velocity = classmethod(velocity)\n",
    "Model.physical = classmethod(physical)\n",
    "Model.jump     = classmethod(jump)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "db272584",
   "metadata": {
    "lines_to_next_cell": 0
   },
   "source": [
    "Method to evolve the solution in time"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "dcf23166",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.818682Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.818522Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.824191Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2025-11-30T19:15:52.823390Z"
    },
    "lines_to_next_cell": 1
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def evolve(space, u_h, limiter=\"MinMod\"):\n",
    "    lu_h = u_h.localFunction()\n",
    "    @gridFunction(space.gridView,name=\"rho\",order=space.order)\n",
    "    def rho(e,x):\n",
    "        lu_h.bind(e)\n",
    "        return lu_h(x)[0]\n",
    "    operator = femDGOperator(Model, space, limiter=limiter) # note: that u_h.space fails since not ufl_space\n",
    "    stepper  = femdgStepper(order=space.order+1 if space.order>0 else 2, operator=operator)\n",
    "    operator.applyLimiter(u_h)\n",
    "\n",
    "    t = 0\n",
    "    saveStep = 0.1\n",
    "    fig = pyplot.figure(figsize=(30,10))\n",
    "    rho.plot(gridLines=\"white\", figure=(fig, 131), colorbar=False, clim=[0.125,1])\n",
    "    c = 1\n",
    "    while t <= 0.3:\n",
    "        operator.setTime(t)\n",
    "        t += stepper(u_h)\n",
    "        if t > saveStep:\n",
    "            print(t)\n",
    "            saveStep += 0.1\n",
    "            rho.plot(gridLines=\"white\", figure=(fig, 131+c), colorbar=False, clim=[0.125,1])\n",
    "            c += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    res = numpy.zeros((2,space.gridView.size(0)))\n",
    "    for i,e in enumerate(space.gridView.elements):\n",
    "        x = e.geometry.center\n",
    "        res[0][i] = x.two_norm\n",
    "        res[1][i] = rho(e,e.geometry.toLocal(x))\n",
    "    return res"
   ]
  },
  {
